# Python testing conventions

The canonical rule content lives in [`coding-rules/rules/testing-python.md`](mdc:coding-rules/rules/testing-python.md) — shared with Claude Code so the tools cannot drift.

When writing or editing Python tests, read and follow `coding-rules/rules/testing-python.md`: pytest with plain assert functions, behavior-driven test names, fixtures and parametrize, built-in fixtures (tmp_path, monkeypatch, caplog), boundary-level mocking, and strict test isolation.
